Description: A very nice hard to find Squier Vintage Modified Jaguar HH in Fiesta Red in a no reserve auction. This is in extremely nice minty condition as being sold as part of an estate. It was purchased new by the original owner. It is a basswood body with rosewood fingerboard and has a very comfortable 24" scale. Stacked concentric controls for volume and tone of each pickup. 9.5" fretboard radius and Duncan Design humbuckers. Originally this guitar sold new on Musicians Friend for $499. They are not available any more - it was a limited run from what I understand and have been able to research. Unlike the other Jaguars, this one has a top loading hard tail bridge that feature adjustable string saddles for excellent intonation. A really fun guitar to play. Paypal payments only, and shipping only to the 48 continental US States. No negative feedback bidders. Thank you!
